---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-15", modifiedDate: "2026-04-04", section: "City Guides" };
const topics = ["city", "market"];
export const title = "Brunswick Dispensary Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Brunswick Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Brunswick, Maine cannabis dispensary guide. 2026 market opportunities, strategic locations, local fee structures, and OCP investment requirements."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
  article={article}
  topics={topics}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Brunswick Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Brunswick, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>Brunswick at a Glance</h2>
      <table aria-label="Brunswick dispensary requirements and market data" caption="Key requirements and market data for opening a dispensary in Brunswick">
        <thead><tr><th scope="col">Requirement</th><th scope="col">Details</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>License Required</strong></td><td>Maine OCP Adult-Use Retail License</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Local Fee</strong></td><td>$2,500 annually</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>School Buffer</strong></td><td>500 ft minimum</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Commercial Rent</strong></td><td>$14-20/sq ft annually</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Current Dispensaries</strong></td><td>3-4 (moderate)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Brunswick?</h2>
      <p>Brunswick is the largest community in mid-coast Maine. About 20,000 people live here year-round. Bowdoin College brings another 1,800 students and hundreds of faculty. The town has a historic downtown, strong local economy, and easy access via I-295 and Route 1.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="The Bowdoin Factor" type="info">
      Bowdoin College brings a young, educated, cannabis-friendly demographic to Brunswick. Students and faculty tend to be early adopters. They care about product quality and are willing to pay for it. This is a premium market.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Market Data</h2>
      <table aria-label="Brunswick dispensary market data" caption="Market demographics and competitive landscape for Brunswick Maine dispensary opportunity">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>City Population</td><td>20,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>College</td><td>Bowdoin College (1,800 students)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Moderate (3-4 dispensaries)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>Route 1, I-295</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Income</td><td>Above Maine average</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The Bowdoin Opportunity</h2>
      <p>Bowdoin College students and faculty are a distinct customer segment. They skew younger. They are generally progressive on cannabis issues. They tend to value quality over price.</p>
      <p>This demographic is not as seasonal as tourist-driven markets. College terms create predictable traffic patterns. Parents visiting students during events create occasional spikes.</p>
      <p>Position your dispensary as a quality-focused operation. Emphasize product knowledge, strain variety, and a welcoming atmosphere. The Brunswick customer will research your menu before visiting.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Rules</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>OCP Adult-Use Retail License required</li>
        <li>Local annual fee: $2,500</li>
        <li>500-foot minimum from schools</li>
        <li>Commercial zoning only</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations in Brunswick</h2>
      <table aria-label="Brunswick recommended dispensary locations" caption="Recommended areas and rent benchmarks for Brunswick dispensary locations">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Area</th><th>Pros</th><th>Rent/Sq Ft</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Maine Street</strong></td><td>Historic downtown, college proximity</td><td>$16-20</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Cook's Corner</strong></td><td>Shopping area, suburban</td><td>$14-17</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Route 1</strong></td><td>Highway access, regional draw</td><td>$12-15</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Location Tip" type="tip">
      Maine Street in downtown Brunswick puts you closest to the college crowd. If your brand targets young adults and quality-focused consumers, that location is worth the premium rent. Route 1 is better for driving traffic from surrounding towns.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Nearby Markets</h2>
      <p>Brunswick's mid-coast location gives access to a broad regional customer base:</p>
      <table aria-label="Brunswick nearby opportunities">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>City</th><th>Distance</th><th>Status</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><a href="/guides/lewiston-dispensary-guide">Lewiston</a></td><td>30 miles</td><td>Open</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/guides/augusta-dispensary-guide">Augusta</a></td><td>30 miles</td><td>Open</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/guides/portland-dispensary-guide">Portland</a></td><td>35 miles</td><td>Open</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Real Estate Considerations</h2>
      <p>Brunswick has three primary commercial zones worth considering. Maine Street in downtown is the heart of the community. It attracts locals, college visitors, and tourists who come for the bookstores and restaurants. Cook's Corner is the suburban shopping area near the mall. Route 1 runs the length of the town and catches regional traffic from surrounding communities.</p>
      <p>Square footage for a dispensary typically runs 1,200-1,800 square feet. In Brunswick, commercial rent ranges from $12-$20 per square foot annually depending on location. Downtown Maine Street commands the highest rents. Route 1 locations cost less but have less foot traffic. Cook's Corner offers a middle ground with good parking.</p>
      <p>The 500-foot school buffer affects certain parcels near Morse High School and the middle school on Industry Road. Verify your chosen location against these before signing a lease.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What Makes Brunswick Different</h2>
      <p>Brunswick is not a tourist destination in the way Kittery or Portland are. Your customer base is primarily local. That changes how you should think about marketing and customer retention. Local customers come back repeatedly. They talk to their neighbors. They write reviews.</p>
      <p>A dispensary in Brunswick lives or dies on reputation within the local community. One bad experience spreads by word of mouth. One memorable experience does too. Invest in making every customer feel known and respected. Reward loyalty. Train your budtenders to remember regulars and their preferences.</p>
      <p>The Bowdoin College connection matters beyond just student customers. Faculty and staff often have higher disposable income. They are community leaders. If your dispensary earns their trust, the entire local network benefits from their recommendations.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Startup Costs</h2>
      <table aria-label="Brunswick dispensary investment range">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Range</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>License + Local Fees</td><td>$10,000-20,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Buildout (1,500 sq ft)</td><td>$150,000-250,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Inventory</td><td>$50,000-100,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Working Capital</td><td>$50,000-100,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>$300,000-400,000</strong></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Mid-coast Maine's largest community with above-average income</li>
        <li>Bowdoin College brings a young, quality-focused customer base</li>
        <li>Maine Street downtown targets the college demographic</li>
        <li>Route 1 reaches customers from surrounding towns</li>
        <li>Total startup: $300K-$400K</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine OCP</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">License Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-locations/">Maine Market Overview</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>Informational only. Verify current local fees and zoning with the Town of Brunswick.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: #1a1a1a; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  .fact-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .fact-box h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box table { margin: 0; }
</style>
